Former Gatanga MP Peter Kenneth has said he will soon reveal the county whose governorship he will vie for in the 2017 general election.Kenneth, a 2013 presidential candidate under the Kenya National Congress party, said he will make the decision in a few weeks. The decision will come very soon after consultations. I am trying to manage other expectations before making the announcement," he said.But he added: Nairobi is dirtier than ever before. Anybody can manage the city better than what my friend (Governor Evans) Kidero."Murang a, Nakuru and Nyandarua are the other counties Kenneth is said to be considering.Read: Uhuru discusses politics with Peter Kenneth in Murang'aAlso read: Youths ask Peter Kenneth to bid for Murang'a governor in 2017The politician, who once served as planning assistant minister, also hinted that he will quit his party for Jubilee.Kenneth said a lot of ill-advised propaganda has followed his declaration of support for President Uhuru Kenyatta next year.On corruption, he said anybody found guilty should be remanded, not allowed to roam free and fight court processes.He spoke at Dandora s African Independent Pentecostal Church of Africa (AIPCA) in Nairobi on Sunday.Embakasi North MP James Gakuya urged Kenneth to vie for the seat in Nairobi. Come to Nairobi and save us from resource mismanagement, Gakuya said and asked the people to vote for those who have good fianncial management records."As Jubilee we are ready to vote for you at the party primaries," he said.Dandora MCA Charles Thuo demanded that Kenneth immediately declare his interest for Nairobi governor.Read: Jubilee MCAs welcome Peter Kenneth to run for Nairobi governor[VIDEO] Peter Kenneth sets eyes on race for Nairobi governor, to support Uhuru in 2017 poll